===Etymology===
From {{inh|en|enm|Affrike}}, from {{der|en|fro|Affrique}}, {{m|fro|Affrike}}, from {{der|en|la|Āfrica}}, from {{m|la|Āfrī}}, singular {{m|la|Āfer}} (inhabitant of the [[w:Ancient Carthage|country of Carthage]]), in turn either from:
* The {{der|en|xpu|-}} or {{der|en|phn|-}} word {{m|phn|𐤏𐤐𐤓|ts=ʿafar|t=dust}}, which has cognates in other Semitic languages.
* The {{der|en|ber|-}} word {{m|und|ifri|t=cave}}, plural {{m|und|ifran}}, in reference to cave dwellers of Tunisia (see [[w:Tataouine|Tataouine]]).
* {{der|en|grc|ἀ-}} + {{m|grc|φρίκη|g=f}}, meaning "without cold"
* {{cog|la|aprica|t=sunny}}.

