==Latin==
{{wikipedia|Africa|lang=la}}

===Etymology===
Feminine of {{m|la|āfricus}}/{{m|la|Āfricus}}, as a noun elliptic of {{m|la|[[terra]] āfrica/Āfrica|lit=the African land}}. The adjective ''Āfricus'' comes from the name of the ''Āfrī'' (singular {{m|la|Āfer}}), a tribal people of the area near Carthage, by addition of the suffix {{m|la|-icus}}.

The Latin term formed alongside Greek {{m|grc|ἡ [[Ἀφρική]]}}, both terms being attested since the first century.

